    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Fuel and High-pressure Oil Systems
        - Installation - Water In Fuel (WIF) Sensor, Engine Fuel Pressure (EFP) Sensor, and Fuel Heater
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Water In Fuel (WIF) Sensor, Engine Fuel Pressure (EFP) Sensor, and Fuel Heater</title>
        <figure id="f3350003082" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK09/K09024.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Fuel filter header assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel inlet port</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">WIF sensor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Water drain valve assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EFP sensor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel heater (optional)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para id="s0724" count="1">Install a new O-ring on the fuel heater and lubricate O-ring with clean diesel
                fuel.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install fuel heater into fuel filter header and finger tighten two M6 x 25 retaining
                bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten two M6 x 25 fuel heater retaining bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_190.xml" xrefid="t335000702">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335000702"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new O-ring on WIF sensor and lubricate O-ring with clean diesel fuel.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install WIF sensor into fuel filter header and tighten to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_190.xml" xrefid="t335000702">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335000702"/>
                or until O-ring contacts fuel filter header and then turn sensor an additional 1/16 of a turn.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new O-ring on the EFP sensor and lubricate O-ring with clean diesel fuel.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install EFP sensor into the bottom of the fuel filter header and tighten to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_190.xml" xrefid="t335000702">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335000702"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect engine sensor harness connectors to the fuel heater, WIF sensor, and EFP sensor.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
